==天文研究==
他最主要的貢獻就是基於[[威廉·赫歇爾|威廉·赫歇爾]]編輯的[[星雲和星團總表|星雲和星團總表]]編輯了現在天文界使用的[[星云和星团新总表|星云和星团新总表]]<ref name="Dryer1888">{{cite journal  | author = Dreyer, J. L. E.  | title = A New General Catalogue of Nebulae and Clusters of Stars,being the Catalogue of the late Sir John F.W. Herschel, Bart., revised, corrected, and enlarged.  | journal = Memoirs of the Royal Astronomical Society  | year = 1888  | volume = 49  | pages = 1–237 | url = http://adsabs.harvard.edu/cgi-bin/nph-bib_query?bibcode=1888MmRAS..49....1D }}</ref>，之後再增補了兩個[[索引星表|索引星表]]<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.springerreference.com/docs/html/chapterdbid/58386.html |title=Dreyer, John Louis Emil, SpringerReference |access-date=2014-10-02 |archive-date=2014-10-06 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006084552/http://www.springerreference.com/docs/html/chapterdbid/58386.html |dead-url=no }}</ref>。

德雷耳還是一位天文學史家。1890年他出版了他的故鄉丹麥的著名天文學家第谷·布拉赫的傳記；晚年他對第谷的出版物和未發表的信件進行整理<ref name="Steinicke"/>。德雷耳於1905年出版的《History of the Planetary Systems from Thales to Kepler》是他的天文史研究成果，雖然部分內容在今日已過時，仍是很好的天文史入門書。之後該書以標題《A History of Astronomy from Thales to Kepler》 重印<ref>[http://www.cambridge.org/ve/academic/subjects/astronomy/history-astronomy-and-cosmology/history-planetary-systems-thales-kepler History of the Planetary Systems From Thales to Kepler, Cambridge University Press] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cambridge.org/ve/academic/subjects/astronomy/history-astronomy-and-cosmology/history-planetary-systems-thales-kepler |date=20150924035826 }}</ref><ref>[https://archive.org/details/AHistoryOfAstronomyFromThalesToKepler A History of Astronomy from Thales to Kepler]</ref>。

德雷耳還和{{link-en|赫伯特·霍爾·特納|Herbert Hall Turner}}共同編寫了第一部英國皇家天文學會發展史書籍《History of the Royal Astronomical Society 1820–1920》，於1923年出版，1987年重印<ref>{{cite web|title=Royal Astronomical Society (RAS)|url=http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/511254/Royal-Astronomical-Society-RAS/93551/Additional-Reading|publisher=[[大英百科全书|Encyclopædia Britannica]]|access-date=2014-10-02|archive-date=2014-10-13|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141013131303/http://www.britannica.com/EBchecked/topic/511254/Royal-Astronomical-Society-RAS/93551/Additional-Reading/|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

